Class Property

java.lang.Object
com.example.Property
public class Property extends Object
This class represents a property with attributes such as geometry, owner, and location. It includes methods to determine adjacency between properties and access property details.

      public Property(int objectid, double par_id, double par_num, double shapeArea, double shapeLength, String geometryStr, int owner, String freguesia, String municipio, String ilha)
      Constructs a Property instance.
      Parameters:
      objectid - The unique identifier for the property.
      par_id - The parcel ID of the property.
      par_num - The parcel number of the property.
      shapeArea - The area of the property.
      shapeLength - The perimeter length of the property.
      geometryStr - The WKT representation of the property geometry.
      owner - The owner ID of the property.
      freguesia - The freguesia (parish) where the property is located.
      municipio - The municipio (municipality) where the property is located.
      ilha - The ilha (island) where the property is located.
